    "Vofe iIM IMTED W E STAXD Published every Friday by Local No 12 UJLWCLOm 425 Winthrop Street Toledo Ohio Editor Melvin Schultz Managing Editor 0 J Pecord Advertising Manager Burny Zawodny Board of Trustee Melvin Schultz Thomas Burke Randolph Gray SUBSCRIPTION RATES One year by mail in advance 8L50 Entered at the Toledo Ohio post office as second class matter under the act of Aug 24 1912 Lsbor Ever since last year when labor forgot to vote the complaints and resentment have increased as legislation and proposed legislation timed at labor have ground through the national and state legislative hoppers Labor hrough its leaders and its press expresses its determination to do something in 1914 to rid the political scene of those who have been unfriendly to it Even now in Toledo and dozens of other cities AFL CIO and Kailroad Brother hood Unions are uniting and preparing for next years election But labor in Toledo is not waiting until 1944 to begin its political action It is tak ing an active interest in the municipal political situation in the belief that good government begins at home and that the place to inaugurate honest and efficient government is right in"
